    {
      "cadence": "weekly",
      "description": "Pick a target \u2014 a Go stdlib package, a small canonical project (BoltDB,\ngroupcache), a daily-use tool (git, ripgrep, fzf), or a piece of a\nlarger system (kube-scheduler, SQLite). Read the README, run the\ntests, find the entry point, trace one path. Don't read top-to-bottom.\nCode is a graph, not a book.\n\nWrite a one-page summary in your notebook: what you learned, what was\nconfusing, what was beautiful. Add 1\u20132 Anki cards. Push the notes\nto your public repo.\n\nPicker: https://sauravsuresh.github.io/long-way-engine/repopick/\nSurfaces one curated repo at a time from the 41-entry seed, with a\nscoped entry point and a concrete question. Click \"Mark complete\"\nwhen this week's read is done to unlock the next one.\n",
      "due": "today at 09:00",
